="D·ªØ li·ªáu / Ch·ªâ s·ªë">Fear & Greed</td>\n                        <td data-label="Gi√° tr·ªã B√°o c√°o">75</td>\n                        <td data-label="Gi√° tr·ªã Real-time (Provided)">75</td>\n                        <td data-label="ƒê·ªô l·ªách">0.00%</td>\n                        <td data-label="Tr·∫°ng th√°i" style="color: var(--positive-color);">‚úÖ PASS</td>\n                    </tr>\n                </tbody>\n            </table>\n        </div>\n        <p><strong>K·∫øt qu·∫£ ki·ªÉm tra: PASS</strong></p>\n        <p>T·∫•t c·∫£ c√°c d·ªØ li·ªáu quan tr·ªçng trong b√°o c√°o ƒë·ªÅu n·∫±m trong ng∆∞·ª°ng sai l·ªách ch·∫•p nh·∫≠n ƒë∆∞·ª£c (ho·∫∑c r·∫•t g·∫ßn) so v·ªõi d·ªØ li·ªáu th·ªùi gian th·ª±c ƒë∆∞·ª£c cung c·∫•p. ƒêi·ªÅu n√†y kh·∫≥ng ƒë·ªãnh t√≠nh ch√≠nh x√°c c·ªßa c√°c s·ªë li·ªáu c·ªët l√µi trong b√°o c√°o, m·∫∑c d√π ph·∫ßn l·ªõn n·ªôi dung d·ª±a tr√™n m√¥ ph·ªèng xu h∆∞·ªõng th·ªã tr∆∞·ªùng trong t∆∞∆°ng lai.</p>\n    </div>\n</section>	/*\n * CSS for Crypto Dashboard Report - Theme Colors & Special Styling\n * Scope: #report-container\n * Uses: CSS Variables ONLY from the provided palette\n */\n\n#report-container {\n    /* Set a base text color for the entire report container */\n    color: var(--text-primary);\n}\n\n/* 1. üé® CRYPTO THEME COLORS */\n\n/* General classes for positive and negative values across the report */\n#report-container .crypto-positive {\n    color: var(--positive-color); /* Success green */\n}\n\n#report-container .crypto-negative {\n    color: var(--negative-color); /* Danger red */\n}\n\n/* Accent colors for specific cryptocurrencies in text, if applied as classes */\n#report-container .bitcoin-accent {\n    color: var(--icon-color-btc); /* Bitcoin orange */\n}\n\n#report-container .ethereum-accent {\n    color: var(--icon-color-eth); /* Ethereum blue */\n}\n\n/* 2. üìä DATA VISUALIZATION COLORS */\n\n/* Table data coloring for positive/negative values (e.g., in validation table) */\n#report-container td.positive {\n    color: var(--positive-color);\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n#report-container td.negative {\n    color: var(--negative-color);\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n/* Hover effect for table rows */\n#report-container table.crypto-table tbody tr:hover {\n    background-color: var(--table-row-hover-bg);\n}\n\n/* 3. üî• SPECIAL CONTENT STYLING */\n\n/* Fear & Greed Index text value styling */\n#report-container #fear-greed-text-analysis strong {\n    color: var(--fng-greed-color); /* Based on the example value 75 ("Tham lam") */\n    font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n/* Bull/Bear/Sideway card styling for "C√°c K·ªãch B·∫£n C√≥ Th·ªÉ X·∫£y Ra" section */\n/* NOTE: These classes (.bull-scenario-card, .sideway-card-card, .bear-scenario-card)\n   are expected to be added to the respective .report-card divs in the HTML for proper application. */\n#report-container .bull-scenario-card {\n    background-color: var(--bull-card-bg);\n    border-left: 5px solid var(--positive-color); /* Visual accent for positive scenario */\n}\n\n#report-container .sideway-card-card {\n    background-color: var(--sideway-card-bg);\n    border-left: 5px solid var(--neutral-color); /* Visual accent for neutral/sideways scenario */\n}\n\n#report-container .bear-scenario-card {\n    background-color: var(--bear-card-bg);\n    border-left: 5px solid var(--negative-color); /* Visual accent for negative scenario */\n}\n\n/* Support/Resistance levels highlighting */\n/* NOTE: These classes (.support-level, .resistance-level) are expected to be\n   added to the relevant price values in the HTML (e.g., <span class="support-level">$115,000</span>). */\n#report-container .support-level {\n    color: var(--positive-color); /* Green for support levels */\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n#report-container .resistance-level {\n    color: var(--negative-color); /* Red for resistance levels */\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n/* Price change indicators (e.g., "gi·∫£m 2.41%") */\n/* NOTE: These classes (.price-change-positive, .price-change-negative) are expected to be\n   added to the relevant percentage values in the HTML. */\n#report-container .price-change-positive {\n    color: var(--positive-color);\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n#report-container .price-change-negative {\n    color: var(--negative-color);\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n/* Volume spike highlighting for the total volume value */\n#report-container #volume-text-analysis strong {\n    color: var(--accent-color); /* Highlight the total volume */\n    font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n/* 4. üí° CONTENT-SPECIFIC HIGHLIGHTS */\n\n/* General styling for strong tags to make them stand out */\n#report-container strong {\n    color: var(--text-primary); /* Default strong color, can be overridden by more specific rules below */\n}\n\n/* Specific strong tag emphasis in Executive Summary for key numbers */\n#report-container #executive-summary-section strong {\n    color: var(--text-accent); /* Accent color for key numbers in summary */\n}\n\n/* Bitcoin Dominance text emphasis */\n#report-container #btc-dominance-text-analysis strong {\n    color: var(--icon-color-btc); /* Use Bitcoin's specific color for its dominance value */\n    font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n/* Bitcoin Price text emphasis */\n#report-container #btc-price-text-analysis strong {\n    color: var(--accent-color); /* Use accent color for the Bitcoin price value */\n    font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n/* RSI text emphasis */\n#report-container #rsi-text-analysis strong {\n    color: var(--rsi-neutral-color); /* Use neutral color for RSI value in neutral range */\n    font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n/* Styling for crypto names in headings (e.g., Bitcoin, Ethereum) */\n/* NOTE: These classes (.btc-heading, .eth-heading) are expected to be\n   added to the relevant h3 elements in the HTML. */\n#report-container .btc-heading {\n    color: var(--icon-color-btc);\n}\n\n#report-container .eth-heading {\n    color: var(--icon-color-eth);\n}\n\n/* Special styling for breaking news list items with custom bullet points */\n#report-container #breaking-news-impact-section ul {\n    list-style-type: none; /* Remove default bullet */\n    padding-left: 0; /* Adjust padding if needed after removing default list style */\n}\n\n#report-container #breaking-news-impact-section ul li {\n    color: var(--text-secondary); /* Softer text color for list items */\n    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Spacing between list items */\n    position: relative;\n    padding-left: 1.5em; /* Space for custom bullet */\n}\n\n#report-container #breaking-news-impact-section ul li::before {\n    content: '‚ö° '; /* Custom lightning bolt bullet */\n    color: var(--accent-color); /* Accent color for the bullet */\n    position: absolute;\n    left: 0;\n    top: 0;\n}\n\n/* Emphasis for card titles (h3 within report-card) */\n#report-container .report-card h3 {\n    color: var(--text-accent); /* Accent color for card sub-headings */\n}\n\n/* Emphasis for scenario titles (h4 within report-card) */\n#report-container .report-card h4 {\n    color: var(--text-primary); /* Primary text color for scenario titles */\n}\n\n/* General list item styling for better readability */\n#report-container ul li {\n    color: var(--text-secondary);\n    line-height: 1.6;\n}\n\n/* Specific styling for the "K·∫øt qu·∫£ ki·ªÉm tra: PASS" text in data validation */\n#report-container #data-validation-section p strong {\n    color: var(--positive-color);\n}	// report.js\n\n/**\n * Helper function to extract chart data from HTML comments.\n * It searches for a comment node immediately preceding the container element\n * and parses the JSON string within it.\n * @param {string} containerId - The ID of the HTML element that will contain the chart.\n * @returns {object|null} The parsed chart data object, or null if not found/parsed.\n */\nfunction getChartDataFromComment(containerId) {\n    const container = document.getElementById(containerId);\n    if (!container) return null;\n\n    let prevNode = container.previousSibling;\n    // Loop backwards to find the comment, in case there are other non-element nodes (like text nodes)\n    while (prevNode && prevNode.nodeType !== Node.COMMENT_NODE) {\n        prevNode = prevNode.previousSibling;\n    }\n\n    if (prevNode && prevNode.nodeType === Node.COMMENT_NODE) {\n        const commentText = prevNode.nodeValue.trim();\n        const prefix = "CHART_DATA: ";\n        if (commentText.startsWith(prefix)) {\n            try {\n                const jsonString = commentText.substring(prefix.length);\n                return JSON.parse(jsonString);\n            } catch (e) {\n                console.error(`Error parsing chart data for ${containerId}:`, e);\n                return null;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Initializes and draws the Fear & Greed Gauge chart.\n * @param {'vi'|'en'} language - The desired language for chart labels.\n */\nfunction initializeFearGreedGauge_report(language) {\n    const lang = language;\n    const id = lang === 'en' ? 'fear-greed-gauge-container-en' : 'fear-greed-gauge-container';\n    const container = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (!container) return;\n\n    const chartData = getChartDataFromComment(id);\n    if (!chartData || chartData.type !== 'gauge') {\n        console.warn(`No valid gauge chart data found for ${id}`);\n        return;\n    }\n\n    const value = chartData.value;\n\n    // Vietnamese labels/config\n    const config_vi = {\n        min: chartData.config.min,\n        max: chartData.config.max,\n        segments: [\n            {limit: 20, color: 'var(--fng-extreme-fear-color)', label: 'C·ª±c k·ª≥ s·ª£ h√£i'},\n            {limit: 40, color: 'var(--fng-fear-color)', label: 'S·ª£ h√£i'},\n            {limit: 60, color: 'var(--fng-neutral-color)', label: 'Trung l·∫≠p'},\n            {limit: 80, color: 'var(--fng-greed-color)', label: 'Tham lam'},\n            {limit: 100, color: 'var(--fng-extreme-greed-color)', label: 'C·ª±c k·ª≥ tham lam'}\n        ]\n    };\n\n 